data.title: Nathan Nuñez - Football
data.meta_description:
Nathan Nuñez (44) Linebacker  - SENIOR (2018)
Saw action in seven of the 10 games … first career tackle went for a one-yard loss in the 41-0 blanking of Georgetown
data.text:
SENIOR (2018)

Saw action in seven of the 10 games … first career tackle went for a one-yard loss in the 41-0 blanking of Georgetown in the season opener ... also had an assisted tackle on kickoff coverage in the shutout win over Sacred Heart.

JUNIOR (2017)

Took the field in the season-opening 38-7 victory at Stetson.

SOPHOMORE (2016)

Missed the season with an injury.

FRESHMAN (2015)

Made a brief appearance in the 49-7 win over Sacred Heart for his first varsity action.

HIGH SCHOOL

Two-time all-county selection who posted 84 tackles as a senior ... had four stops for a loss, 12 sacks and forced a pair of fumbles while making all-conference first team ... recorded 76 tackles as a junior with three for a loss and two interceptions ... another combo linebacker-tight end ... captained team as a senior ... also wrestled one year ... National Football Foundation Scholar-Athlete for Northeast Ohio and Academic All-Ohio for Division 1.
